        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/dfb087/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-02T15:10:39.137Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I would personally be in favor of removing swipe to archive altogether.</p>\n<p>The overwhelming majority of times I use it is accidental. It is even worse given that when you‚Äôre using a folder that is not the ‚Äúall conversations‚Äù folder, you can‚Äôt even get to the archive anymore by scrolling, making the process of finding and dearchiving the conversation even more painful.</p>\n<p>I‚Äôve also had to deal with older relatives archiving by accident and struggling to find the conversation again.</p>\n<p>Having to stretch my hand to be able to reach the scrolling folder selector is uncomfortable, being able to just swipe a couple of times instead would be much more straightforward.</p>\n<p>This topic: <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/include-archived-chats-option-for-folders/72628/6\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Include archived chats option for folders - #6 by Meteor0id</a> shows the issue I have with Archival and folders not working well together, exacerbating the problems that accidental swiping cause.</p>",
